const GGR_ITEMS: ItemTemplate[] = [
  { name: 'Guild Keyrune', category: 'magic', weight: 1, description: 'Wondrous item, rarity varies by guild (requires attunement by a member of the relevant guild). A ceremonial, stylized key about 1 foot long, carved from stone. Speak the command word and place it on the ground: it transforms into a creature specific to your guild (Azorius: giant eagle 1 hr; Boros: veteran human 8 hrs; Dimir: intellect devourer 24 hrs; Golgari: giant scorpion 6 hrs; Gruul: ceratok/rhinoceros 1 hr; Izzet: galvanic weird 3 hrs; Orzhov: winged thrull 2 hrs; Rakdos: cackler 1 hr; Selesnya: dire wolf 8 hrs; Simic: category 1 krasis 5 hrs). The creature is friendly to you and follows your commands. Reverts if it drops to 0 HP or you speak the command word again. Can\'t transform again for 36 hours after reverting.' },
  { name: 'Guild Signet', category: 'magic', weight: 0, description: 'Ring, uncommon (requires attunement). This ring bears the symbol of a guild and allows you to cast one spell closely associated with that guild. The ring has 3 charges and regains 1d3 expended charges daily at dawn. While wearing it, you can expend 1 charge to cast the associated spell (save DC 13): Azorius: ensnaring strike; Boros: heroism; Dimir: disguise self; Golgari: entangle; Gruul: compelled duel; Izzet: chaos bolt; Orzhov: command; Rakdos: hellish rebuke; Selesnya: charm person; Simic: expeditious retreat.' },
  { name: "Illusionist's Bracers", category: 'magic', weight: 1, description: 'Wondrous item, very rare (requires attunement by a spellcaster). While wearing these bracers, whenever you cast a cantrip, you can use a bonus action on the same turn to cast that cantrip a second time.' },
  { name: 'Mizzium Apparatus', category: 'magic', weight: 8, description: 'Wondrous item, uncommon (requires attunement by a sorcerer, warlock, or wizard). A collection of leather straps, flexible tubing, glass cylinders, and plates made from mizzium, all assembled into a harness. You can use it as an arcane focus. In addition, you can attempt to cast a spell you don\'t know or have prepared. The spell must be on your class\'s spell list and of a level for which you have a spell slot. You must provide the spell\'s components and expend a slot. Before resolving it, make an Intelligence (Arcana) check (DC 10 + 2× the slot level). Success: cast as normal. Fail: roll on a wild magic table for that slot level to determine what happens instead.' },
  { name: 'Mizzium Armor', category: 'magic', weight: 0, description: 'Armor (medium or heavy, not hide), rare. This suit is reinforced with mizzium. While wearing it, any critical hit against you becomes a normal hit. In addition, when you are subjected to a magical effect that allows you to make a Strength or Constitution saving throw to take only half damage, you instead take no damage if you succeed on the saving throw.' },
  { name: 'Mizzium Mortar', category: 'magic', weight: 0, description: 'Wondrous item, rare. This short tube is made from mizzium. It has 4 charges and regains 1d4 expended charges daily at dawn. Molten Spray (1 charge): action, 30-foot cone, each creature makes DC 15 Dex save or takes 5d4 fire damage (half on success). Mizzium Bombard (3 charges): action, target a point within 60 feet, 20-foot-radius 40-foot-high cylinder, each creature makes DC 15 Dex save or takes 5d8 fire damage (half on success).' },
  { name: "Pariah's Shield", category: 'magic', weight: 6, description: 'Armor (shield), rare (requires attunement). You gain a +1 bonus to AC for every two allies within 5 feet of you (maximum +3) while you wield this shield. This bonus is in addition to the shield\'s normal bonus to AC. When a creature you can see within 5 feet of you takes damage, you can use your reaction to take that damage instead of the creature taking it. When you do so, the damage type changes to force.' },
  { name: 'Moodmark Paint', category: 'magic', weight: 0, description: 'Wondrous item, common. This thick, black paint is stored in a small jar with enough paint to apply to one creature. Applying it takes 1 minute. For the next 8 hours, the marks change to reflect your mental state. A creature that can see you and succeeds on a DC 10 Wisdom (Insight) check can discern whether you are happy, sad, angry, disgusted, surprised, or afraid, as well as the main source of that emotion. A dark elf has advantage on this check.' },
  { name: 'Peregrine Mask', category: 'magic', weight: 0, description: 'Wondrous item, very rare (requires attunement). While wearing this winged helm, you have a flying speed of 60 feet. In addition, you have advantage on initiative rolls.' },
  { name: 'Pyroconverger', category: 'magic', weight: 5, description: 'Wondrous item, uncommon (requires attunement). An Izzet-made flamethrower. As an action, cause it to project fire in a 10-foot cone. Each creature in that area must make a DC 13 Dexterity saving throw, taking 4d6 fire damage on a failed save or half as much on success. Each time you use the pyroconverger, roll a d10 and add the number of times you\'ve used it since your last long rest. If the total is 11 or higher, it malfunctions: you take 4d6 fire damage and can\'t use it again until you finish a long rest.' },
  { name: 'Rakdos Riteknife', category: 'magic', weight: 1, description: 'Weapon (dagger), legendary (requires attunement). You gain a +1 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic weapon. Whenever you slay a creature with an attack using the dagger, that creature\'s soul is imprisoned inside the dagger (max 5 souls). For each imprisoned soul, your attacks with the dagger deal an extra 1d4 necrotic damage. Siphon Vitality: bonus action, release any number of souls to regain 1d10 HP per soul released. Annihilation: if the dagger holds five souls, you can use your reaction immediately after hitting a creature to release all five souls. If the target has fewer than 75 HP, it must succeed on a DC 15 Constitution saving throw or die. If it dies, you can\'t use this property again until you finish a long rest.' },
  { name: 'Skyblinder Staff', category: 'magic', weight: 4, description: 'Staff, uncommon (requires attunement). You gain a +1 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic quarterstaff. While holding it, you also gain a +1 bonus to spell attack rolls. If a flying creature you can see within 30 feet of you makes an attack roll against you, you can use your reaction to hold the staff aloft and cause it to flare with light. The attacker has disadvantage on the attack roll, and it must succeed on a DC 13 Constitution saving throw or be blinded until the start of its next turn.' },
  { name: "Spies' Murmur", category: 'magic', weight: 0, description: 'Wondrous item, uncommon (requires attunement). This headpiece, crafted from dark metal, is worn curved around the ear. If you know another creature wearing a spies\' murmur and that creature is within 1 mile of you, you can communicate with each other telepathically. As a bonus action, you can allow that creature to hear everything you hear for 1 hour. You can end this effect as a bonus action, and it ends if you\'re incapacitated.' },
  { name: 'Sunforger', category: 'magic', weight: 2, description: 'Weapon (warhammer), rare (requires attunement). You gain a +2 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic weapon. As an action, you can hurl the weapon up to 120 feet to a point you can see. When it reaches that point, it vanishes in an explosion. Each creature in a 20-foot-radius sphere centered on that point must make a DC 15 Dexterity saving throw, taking 6d6 fire damage on a failed save or half as much on success. Afterward, you can use an action to cause the weapon to reappear in your empty hand. You can\'t cause it to explode again until you finish a short or long rest.' },
  { name: 'Sword of the Paruns', category: 'magic', weight: 3, description: 'Weapon (longsword), very rare (requires attunement). You gain a +1 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic weapon. Additionally, once on each of your turns while you\'re holding the sword, you can use one of the following properties: after the Attack action, enable one creature within 60 feet to use its reaction to make one weapon attack; after the Dash action, enable one creature within 60 feet to use its reaction to move up to its speed; after the Dodge action, enable one creature within 60 feet to use its reaction to gain the benefits of the Dodge action.' },
  { name: 'Voyager Staff', category: 'magic', weight: 4, description: 'Staff, very rare (requires attunement by a spellcaster). You gain a +1 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic quarterstaff. While you hold it, you also gain a +1 bonus to spell attack rolls. The staff has 10 charges. While holding it, you can use an action to expend 1 or more of its charges to cast one of the following spells (save DC your spell save DC): banishment (4 charges), blink (3 charges), misty step (2 charges), passwall (5 charges), or teleport (7 charges). The staff regains 1d6 + 4 expended charges daily at dawn. If you expend the last charge, roll a d20. On a 1, the staff vanishes forever.' },
];

